<b>Diet care for Eczema</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Since inflammation is believed to cause eczema in many cases, it is advisable to avoid all inflammation-causing foods which include nuts, milk and wheat.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Anti-inflammatory foods containing antioxidants such as probiotics can help to tackle eczema by strengthening the immune system. Some of the favourable foods include yoghurt, khimchi, kombucha and sauerkraut.</span>

